# Architecture

Before implementing any feature:

1. Analyze the existing architecture.
2. Explain where the feature belongs.
3. Reuse existing modules before creating new ones.
4. Extend existing components before duplicating functionality.
5. Avoid unnecessary abstractions.

## Layer map

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Routes (thin) | `src/app/` | Routing, layouts, BFF route handlers only |
| Business logic | `src/features/` | Vertical slices (UI, hooks, api, types) |
| Shared UI | `src/components/` | Presentational primitives and composites |
| Infrastructure | `src/lib/` | API clients, design system, utils, db/ai stubs |
| Providers | `src/providers/` | App-wide React context |
| Global hooks | `src/hooks/` | Generic hooks with no business logic |
| Shared types | `src/types/` | Cross-feature domain vocabulary |

Never place business logic inside `src/app/` routes. Keep pages thin.

Prefer feature modules over generic folders. Prefer composition over duplication.

## Feature module shape

```
features/<name>/
  components/   hooks/   api/   types.ts   utils.ts   index.ts
```

Cross-feature imports go through public `index.ts` barrels only.

## Dependencies

Before adding a dependency:

- Explain why it is needed.
- Prefer existing project dependencies.

## Design system (required)

Always use `src/lib/design-system/` and `src/styles/tokens.css`.

Never hardcode colors, spacing, typography, motion, or border radius in components.
Use semantic tokens: `toneClasses`, `surfaces`, `labelClass`, `chartColors`, etc.

## Completion summary (required)

Every implementation must summarize:

- Architecture decisions
- Files created / modified
- Dependencies added
- Technical debt introduced
- Future improvements
